description: One person died in a multi-vehicle collision on Lakeville Highway in Petaluma this morning, a REDCOM fire and emergency center dispatcher said.
maintext: One person died in a multi-vehicle collision on Lakeville Highway in Petaluma this morning, a REDCOM fire and emergency center dispatcher said.The collision was reported at 7:15 a.m., the dispatcher said.Lakeville Highway between Browns Lane and the South McDowellBoulevard extension are closed and side roads in the area are blocked, according to the California Highway Patrol.
title: Person killed in multi-vehicle crash in Petaluma
